'''''The Bro Code: How Contemporary Culture Creates Sexist Men''''' is a [[documentary]] created by Thomas Keith in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Bro Code|url=http://www.mediaed.org/cgi-bin/commerce.cgi?preadd=action&key=246|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref><ref> {{cite web | title = ‘Bro Code’ encourages open discussion on existing societal effects of sexism |publisher=Daily Nebraskan: Arts And Entertainment | url = http://www.dailynebraskan.com/arts_and_entertainment/article_0cce5106-23d0-11e2-aba4-0019bb30f31a.html | accessdate = 2015-02-27 }} </ref><ref> {{cite web | title = City Times : Film reminds students that sexism still exists |publisher=City Times | url = http://www.sdcitytimes.com/news/2012/10/09/film-reminds-students-that-sexism-still-exists/ | accessdate = 2015-02-27 }} </ref>
The film has been described as a treatise on [[misogyny]].<ref name=tarrant>{{cite book|title=Men Speak Out: Views on Gender, Sex, and Power| last1=Tarrant|first1=Shira|publisher=Routledge|location=New York, New York|isbn=9780415521086|page=275|edition=2nd}}</ref>
==Biographical information on filmmaker==
Thomas Keith is a professor at [[California State Polytechnic University, Pomona|California Polytechnic University]] and [[Claremont Graduate University]] where he teaches [[philosophy]] and [[gender studies]]. His specific areas of study include: American philosophy, [[race (human categorization)|race]], [[Social class|class]], and [[gender]].<ref> In 2017, he published the book Masculinities in Contemporary American Culture: An Intersectional Approach to the Complexities and Challenges of Male Identity (Routledge Press). </https://www.amazon.com/Masculinities-Contemporary-American-Culture-Intersectional/dp/1138818070> {{cite web | title = Dr. Tom Keith |publisher=Tom Keith | url = http://www.tomkeith.net/biography | accessdate = 2015-02-27 }} </ref><ref>{{cite web | title = The Bro Code |publisher=Media Education Foundation | url = http://www.mediaed.org/cgi-bin/commerce.cgi?preadd=action&key=246#filmmaker-about | accessdate = 2015-02-27 }}</ref>
